albums.notes: It's aight. Kinda trails off after Who Laughs Last. But perhaps my expectations are a big too high after coming off of Long Lost.

albums.name: Long Lost
albums.notes: Usually the skits, short tracks are filler for me, but these were bumped up to Good as they bring the score down too much.

albums.name: I’ll Be Waving as You Drive Away
albums.notes: Aug 9th, 2025 - Album feels a bit more darker than his previous record. I'm not enjoying it as much as I did his previous record despite the praise from critics this record got. Not saying it's bad though.

albums.name: Lonely People With Power
albums.notes: This album has a bit of everything for Deafheaven's catalog. The shoegaze of sunbather, the thrash riffs of Black Brick. It's scary at times, beautiful at times. Awesome record.
